cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Not All Invariants Are Equal: Curating Training Data to Accelerate Program Verification with SLMs"
authors:
  - family-names: Pinto
    given-names: Ido
type: article
year: 2026
url: "https://github.com/idopinto/wonda"
repository-code: "https://github.com/idopinto/wonda"
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  The synthesis of inductive loop invariants is a critical bottleneck in automated
  program verification. We present a rigorous data curation pipeline (WONDA) designed
  to extract high-quality training signals from raw verifier-generated invariants, and
  demonstrate that fine-tuning Small Language Models on this curated dataset yields
  consistent and significant gains on invariant generation and verification tasks.
keywords:
  - loop invariants
  - program verification
  - LLM
  - fine-tuning
  - formal methods
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using the metadata from this file."
